Reasoning: The paper describes a Python package focused on natural language processing and machine learning for legal and regulatory text. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The package includes functionality for segmenting documents, identifying key text, extracting structured information, and building unsupervised and supervised models, which are all relevant to these sub-categories. However, given the focus on natural language processing and information extraction, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
